The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks related to biomedical research and mental health disorders. Specifically, it focuses on retrieval and ranking of PubMed abstracts and extraction of relevant sentences from them, using attention-based neural models and other techniques. This falls under the broad category of NLP and information retrieval (IR) research, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category, as it specifically deals with NLP research. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also highly likely, as the paper deals with retrieval and ranking of relevant documents. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible sub-categories, as the paper uses supervised and unsupervised learning techniques. Finally, cs.DL (Deep Learning) is a possible sub-category, as the paper uses neural models with attention mechanisms.
